children.text: The roof sheets do not overhang the gutter by the correct distance to ensure the roof system can remove the stormwater as intended.
The Victorian Building Authority’s, Guide to Standards and Tolerances clause 6.05 Overhang of roofing (tiles and sheet roofing) states that
‘Sheet roofing is defective if it overhangs the inside face of a gutter by less than 50mm or by more than 65mm’ .
This section of roof sheeting must be rectified in accordance with above.
